 Nigeria’s (top L-R) Leon Balogun, William Ekong, Anthony Nwakaeme, Ikechukwu Ezenwa, Onyinye Ndidi, John Ogu, (bottom L-R) Abdullahi Shehu, Alexander Iwobi, Ola Aina, Oghenekaro Etebo, and Kelechi Iheanacho pose prior to the 2018 FIFA World Cup Group B qualifying football match between Algeria and Nigeria at the Chahid Hamlaou Stadium in Constantine on November 10, 2017. RYAD KRAMDI / AFP  The Krstajic-tutored team is in Group E with Brazil, Switzerland, Costa Rica, and Manchester United’s midfielder, Nemanja Matic, would lead the World Cup-bound team in the two friendly games. Others included in the team are English Premier League top players like Dusan Tadic of Southampton, Cardiff’s Marko Grujic, and Aleksandar Mitrovic of Fulham.Red Star Belgrade central defender, Vujadin Savic, makes his debut after being handed his first call up in their preparation towards achieving success at the World Cup. Former Manchester City left back now at Roma, Aleksandar Kolarov, is also in the Coach Krstajic’s team, as he has a date with his former team mate, Kelechi Iheanacho, named in the Nigerian squad by Coach Gernot Rohr for the friendly.Eddy Onazi, who once played for Lazio, will meet former teammate, Sergei Milinkovic-Savic, while Torino’s Adem Ljajic is also another top player for the Serbians.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .